<item>
            <title>[CXF-4618] DataSourceProvider is not closing inputstream acquired from DataSource</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4618</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a REST method returns a DataSource, e.g.:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@GET&lt;br/&gt;
public DataSource getFile() { ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...the CXF JAX-RS framework obtains an inputstream from the datasource but does  close the stream after use.  This is noticeable on windows environments for the case of a provided FileDataSource, since the underlying file cannot be deleted while this file handle remains open.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tracked down the problem to the writeTo() method of org.apache.cxf.jaxrs.provider.DataSourceProvider and will attach a proposed patch.&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
